We recommended that the General Services Office:

Renew PARs every three years and every time there is a change in custodianship;



Ensure that the end-user duly acknowledge receipt of properties by signing in the “Received from” portion and the GSO sign the “issued by” portion of the PAR to pinpoint responsibility over the PPE;

Ensure that the PARs are properly numbered and dated in accordance with the numbering under Section 58 of GAM for LGUs Volume II to serve as controlling measure and to determine when is the next renewal of PARs; and

That the ICS is use to issue tangible items which costs ₱15,000.00 and below and has life of more than one year in accordance with Section 59 of GAM for LGUs Volume II.

We recommended that management to:

a. Determine the last custodian of the PPE which are not found in station;

b. Investigate the cause of the loss and determine the extent of the liability of the officer concerned;

Institute appropriate actions to recover the money value of the lost property from the accountable officer;

Require the LDRRMO to prioritize programs/projects/activities to be funded from the LDRRMF to ensure the readiness of the Municipality in case of calamity;

To ensure that the PPAs will be implemented in an efficient and effective manner to avoid the conduct of similar activities every budget year; and

To coordinate with other agencies providing evacuation facilities for the latter to be equipped with the necessary amenities.

We recommended that management;

To enforce on the contractor for the completion of the paved shoulders of the local roads;

To ensure that the local roads were implemented in accordance with approved POW and in compliance with the above-cited DPWH Department order; and

To require the Project Monitoring Committee/ Project inspectorate team to conduct project inspection prior to approval of the 100% Status of Work Accomplishment (SWA).

