We recommend that Management to:

Require the GSO and the Disposal Committee to conduct physical verification of unserviceable PPE,  to determine the present condition and propose mode of disposal;

Require the Disposal Committee to appraise the unserviceable PPE to be disposed through public auction;

Require the Disposal Committee to file an application for disposal with appropriate documents to the COA;

Ensure that the required procedure in the disposal of the government property will be strictly followed before the disposal is made;

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting journal entry to derecognize the destroyed PPE in the books of account; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to provide adequate disclosures in the Notes to FS on the unserviceable PPE.

We recommend that management to:

Determine the last custodian of the PPE which are not found in station;


Investigate the cause of the loss and determine the extent of the liability of the officer concerned;


Institute appropriate actions to recover the money value of the lost property from the accountable officer; and


Require the Municipal Accountant to provide adequate disclosures in the Notes to FS.

We recommend that management to:

Require all the debtors, officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances immediately by issuing demand letters;

Institute appropriate legal sanction against concerned officials or employees, by withholding or suspension of their salaries;

Exert all efforts to expedite liquidation of cash advances of officers and employees who have already died or no longer in service. After exhausting efforts to have these accounts settled and no other alternative procedures are available, management may file a request for write-off (except for the cash advances for Confidential Expenses) in accordance with the provision of Section 4 of Rule VIII, 2009 Revised Rules and Provisions of the Commission on Audit dated September 15, 2009; and

Comply with the requirements set forth under COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016 which provides for the Guidelines and Procedures on the Write-off of Dormant Receivable Accounts, Unliquidated Cash Advances, and Fund Transfers of National Government Agencies, Local Government Units and Government-Owned and Controlled Corporations.

